Quote:  Karl trusts his tutor enough to bring him his "biscuit box of broken dreams", his stories stored in a Griffins Sampler Box based on tragic events of his childhood.
Notes:  I knew these in the 1930s as "Griffins' Sampler Biscuits". They were sold in fancy packets for a little more than the cost of an ordinary packet and contained a few of each of Griffins' lines, including walnut creams and iced wafers. They were a rare treat for school lunch when your mother was hardpressed to cut lunch for one reason or another - DEH
